<TITLE> 7 arrested in newsman's murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com) -- Turag police have arrested seven professional muggers for the murder of ATN Bangla cameraman. The police recovered senior cameraman Shafikul Islam Mithu's body from Rustampur dam under Turag Police Station on Sunday morning. He had been strangled. Mithu has been since Saturday night while returning home from office. The muggers revealed substantial information related to the case, said the Turag police chief Abu Saleh Md Ansaruddin. He told bdnews24.com that the muggers were apprehended in a special mission that is still underway. They were arrested from Mirpur, Dakkhinkhaan, Uttara, Ashulia and Tongi. But their names were not disclosed in the interest of the investigation. OC Ansaruddin also said that the hijackers had admitted to the police that they generally mug 15-20 people every night. They run a micro bus and private car pretending to commute people to get suitable victims, and then they mug them. A murder case against unidentified miscreants has been filed at Turag Police Station.
